snippet.textDisplay: For Eugene's I would have made kimchi loaded potato skins with lots of cheese and sausage. With Zack, you can mash the potatoes to a puree and then pipe them out of a bag - cut the corner of a sandwich bag and load it with potato and then extrude it into some hot oil. Keith did well! I can't really think of anything to make with salmon. When we cook salmon fillets at home we just bake them with some old bay seasoning or whatever. Actually we buy them already marinated sometimes. If you wanted to break up the fillet (idk why) you can reconstitute it into a burger patty, so yummy!!! Salmon also goes well with pasta, but over rice is good too. Ned made so many different things! The cocktail with simple syrup was pretty impressive, his pronunciation of "sake" less so. Wes is getting big sooo fast!!! I wanna try making tuna meatballs now. Good job trying to share the mental load by making dinner guys, it's hard to plan and cook meals and manage cycling food in and out of the pantry so it doesn't spoil!!! This was a good challenge and it'd be even better if most families made it a habit to share the load. You'll only get better at it!!
